load ../infoflow-declassifier.maude

--- ===================== COVERAGE =====================

--- A privileged release with a TRUSTED (high-integrity) selector, granted, predicate
--- holding, budget remaining -> released to the privileged reader.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-DECLASSIFIER :
  selectorInteg(hi) releaseReq(hi) granted predHolds budget(s 0)
  =>* C:Cfg released(hi) .

--- A refusal that depends only on a fixed PUBLIC budget (lo) is safely observable by
--- the public -- no leak.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-DECLASSIFIER :
  refusalAt(lo) observer(lo) =>* C:Cfg obsOk .

--- The refusal-channel DETECTOR fires: a secret-dependent refusal (hi) observed by
--- the public (lo) is flagged as a leak.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-DECLASSIFIER :
  refusalAt(hi) observer(lo) =>* C:Cfg obsLeak .

--- ===================== BITES =====================

--- Bite (NMIF ON THE SELECTOR): an ATTACKER-STEERED selector (lo) can never drive a
--- PRIVILEGED release (to a hi reader). No adaptive oracle to a privileged reader.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-DECLASSIFIER :
  selectorInteg(lo) releaseReq(hi) granted predHolds budget(s 0)
  =>* released(hi) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite (BUDGET BACKSTOP): an exhausted budget (0) blocks any further release, even
--- with grant and predicate satisfied.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-DECLASSIFIER :
  releaseReq(lo) granted predHolds budget(0)
  =>* released(lo) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite (REFUSAL CHANNEL): a secret-dependent refusal cannot be safely observed by
--- the public -- the refusal itself is a leak, so a budget must be fixed/public, not
--- a data-dependent "refuse when dangerous".
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-DECLASSIFIER :
  refusalAt(hi) observer(lo) =>* obsOk RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite (AUTHORITY, X3): an UNGRANTED release never fires, even with a trusted
--- selector, predicate, and budget.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-DECLASSIFIER :
  selectorInteg(hi) releaseReq(hi) predHolds budget(s 0)
  =>* released(hi) RESIDUAL:Cfg .

--- Bite (PREDICATE): a release whose trusted predicate does NOT hold never fires.
search [1] in WHIPPLESCRIPT-INFOFLOW-DECLASSIFIER :
  releaseReq(lo) granted budget(s 0)
  =>* released(lo) RESIDUAL:Cfg .
